          <p>In Lake Charles, your AC works harder and longer than systems in most parts of the country. From April through October, it runs almost constantly to combat temperatures in the 90s and humidity levels that can exceed 80%. Regular maintenance isn't optionalâ€”it's essential for keeping your system healthy.</p>

          <h2>What's Included in Our AC Tune-Up</h2>
          <p>Our comprehensive tune-up includes a thorough inspection and service of your entire cooling system:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Inspect and clean condenser coils</strong> - Dirty coils reduce efficiency and can cause overheating</li>
            <li><strong>Check refrigerant levels</strong> - Low refrigerant indicates a leak and reduces cooling capacity</li>
            <li><strong>Inspect and clean evaporator coil</strong> - Ensures proper heat transfer and humidity removal</li>
            <li><strong>Check and tighten electrical connections</strong> - Loose connections can cause failures and safety hazards</li>
            <li><strong>Test capacitors and contactors</strong> - These components are common failure points</li>
            <li><strong>Lubricate moving parts</strong> - Reduces friction and wear on motors and bearings</li>
            <li><strong>Check thermostat calibration</strong> - Ensures accurate temperature control</li>
            <li><strong>Inspect ductwork for leaks</strong> - Leaky ducts waste energy and reduce comfort</li>
            <li><strong>Replace or clean air filter</strong> - Dirty filters restrict airflow and reduce efficiency</li>
            <li><strong>Clear condensate drain</strong> - Clogged drains cause water damage and humidity problems</li>
            <li><strong>Check blower motor and fan</strong> - Ensures proper airflow throughout your home</li>
            <li><strong>Test system operation</strong> - Verify proper cooling and cycling</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Benefits of Regular AC Maintenance</h2>
          <ul>
